  <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-800">
    <p class="text-xl font-light leading-relaxed mb-6 text-gray-600">
      The U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) is not just for farmers. In 2026, it is the single largest investor in rural <strong>small business growth</strong>, deploying over <strong>$1.5 billion</strong> in grants and loan guarantees. If your business is located outside a major metro area, you are likely sitting on a goldmine of eligibility that city-based competitors cannot touch.
    </p>

    <h2 id="eligibility-map" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-10 mb-6">Step 1: The "Rural" Litmus Test</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Before you read another word, you must verify your geography. USDA's definition of "rural" is generous. It typically includes:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6 text-gray-700">
      <li>Any area with a population under 50,000.</li>
      <li>Many "suburban" areas that were once rural and haven't been re-classified.</li>
      <li>Tribal lands and colonized territories.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-6 rounded-r-lg mb-8">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-yellow-900 mb-2">📍 The Eligibility Hack</h3>
      <p class="text-yellow-800 text-lg">
        Don't guess. Use the <a href="https://eligibility.sc.egov.usda.gov/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 underline font-bold">USDA Eligibility Map</a>. Enter your address. If it falls in a shaded area, you are ineligible. If it's outside, you are green-lit for <strong>millions in potential funding</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="reap-energy" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Run Your Business on the Sun: REAP Grants</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      The <strong>Rural Energy for America Program (REAP)</strong> is the crown jewel of 2026. Thanks to Inflation Reduction Act funding entensions, REAP is more flush with cash than ever.
    </p>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border border-green-200 shadow-sm relative">
        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 bg-green-500 text-white text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-bl-lg">Most Popular</div>
        <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-green-800 mb-3">REAP Grants (Free Money)</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li><strong>Covers:</strong> Up to <strong>50%</strong> of total project costs.</li>
          <li><strong>Max Award:</strong> $1 Million for renewable energy systems.</li>
          <li><strong>Eligible Projects:</strong> Solar panels, wind turbines, biomass, geothermal, anaerobic digesters.</li>
          <li><strong>Who Qualifies:</strong> Rural small businesses & agricultural producers (farmers).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border border-blue-200 shadow-sm relative">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-blue-800 mb-3">REAP Guaranteed Loans</h3>
         <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
          <li><strong>Covers:</strong> Up to <strong>75%</strong> of project costs.</li>
          <li><strong>Max Amount:</strong> $25 Million.</li>
          <li><strong>Terms:</strong> Standard interest rates but government-backed (easier approval).</li>
          <li><strong>Combo:</strong> You can combine Grant (50%) + Loan (25%) to cover 75% of your project.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-lg">
      <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">⚡ 2026 REAP Strategy: Sustainability as Strategy</h4>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
        Reviewers in 2026 are prioritizing projects that demonstrate <strong>Immediate ROI</strong>. Show how saving $2,000/month on electricity allows you to hire 1 new employee. That "Job Creation" narrative wins the grant.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="vapg-ag" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">From Farm to Brand: Value-Added Producer Grant (VAPG)</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      If you grow a commodity (tomatoes) and sell a commodity (tomatoes), you are a price taker. <br>
      If you grow a commodity (tomatoes) and sell a product (Organic Basil-Infused Marinara Sauce), you are a <strong>Value-Added Producer</strong>.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      The VAPG exists to pay for that transformation. It is one of the few federal grants that funds <strong>Working Capital</strong> (marketing, processing, packaging, payroll).
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="bg-orange-100 p-3 rounded-lg mr-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">💰</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-900">Planning Grant: Up to $75,000</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Pays for a consultant to write a Feasibility Study and Marketing Plan. 100% covered (requires match in time/cash).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex items-start">
        <div class="bg-orange-100 p-3 rounded-lg mr-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">🏭</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-900">Working Capital Grant: Up to $250,000</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-600">Pays for processing costs, marketing campaigns, packaging inventory, and labor to make the new product.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 id="rbdg-business" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">The "Everything Else" Grant: RBDG</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      The <strong>Rural Business Development Grant (RBDG)</strong> is the utility player of rural funding. It is small (typically $10k - $500k) but flexible.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      <strong>Crucial Distinction:</strong> Money technically goes to a non-profit or public body (Town, EDA), which then uses it to help your small business. You need a municipal partner.
    </p>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      <div class="border border-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
         <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">✅ Eligible Uses</h4>
         <ul class="list-disc pl-4 text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
           <li>Training & Technical Assistance</li>
           <li>Acquisition or development of land</li>
           <li>Construction/Renovation of buildings</li>
           <li>Equipment purchase</li>
           <li>Rural transportation improvements</li>
         </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-red-200 p-4 rounded-lg">
         <h4 class="font-bold text-red-800 mb-2">❌ Ineligible Uses</h4>
         <ul class="list-disc pl-4 text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-1">
           <li>Pass-through grants (giving cash directly to business)</li>
           <li>Agricultural production (that's for VAPG)</li>
           <li>Comprehensive planning</li>
           <li>Golf courses or gambling facilities</li>
         </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 id="match-requirements" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">The Catch: Matching Funds Explained</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Almost all USDA grants require a <strong>1:1 Match</strong> (or similar). This means for every $1 the government gives you, you must invest $1.
    </p>
    
    <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-blue-900 mb-4">Don't Panic: "In-Kind" is Your Friend</h3>
      <p class="text-blue-800 mb-4">
        You don't always need cash in the bank. You can often use:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-blue-700">
        <li><strong>Inventory:</strong> The value of the crop you are processing (VAPG).</li>
        <li><strong>Labor:</strong> The time you and your family spend working on the project (Sweat Equity).</li>
        <li><strong>Loans:</strong> A line of credit or bank loan counts as your "cash match."</li>
        <li><strong>Third-Party Contributions:</strong> Discounts or donated services.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 id="application-tips" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">Reviewer Scorecard: How to Win</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      USDA reviewers are often state-level officials who care about <strong>Local Impact</strong>.
    </p>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="text-center p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">🏘️</div>
        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Community Need</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Prove your area is distressed. Use census data showing poverty rates or population decline.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
        <div class="text-3xl mb-2">👷</div>
        <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Job Creation</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">Hard numbers. "Retaining 5 jobs and creating 3 new full-time positions."</p>
      </div>
